      <p><em>Parts 1 and 2 of this essay laid bare the cracks in our educational foundations — from the erosion of academic standards to the outdated age-based progression and the overreliance on standardised testing. In this final part, I ask how we can build an education system that values character, creativity, and emotional intelligence as much as academic performance.</em></p>
